{{distinguish|Alfredo Angeli|Alfredo De Angelis}} {{Infobox Vice President |name= Alfredo de Angeli |image= De Ángeli enero 2016 (cropped).jpg |office= Argentine Senator for Entre Ríos |term_start= 10 December 2013 |term_end= |birth_date= {{Birth date and age|1956|07|01}} |birth_place= [[María Grande]], [[Argentina]] |profession= |party= |otherparty= |alma_mater= |signature= |footnotes= }} '''Alfredo de Angeli''' (born July 1, 1956) is a rural leader of the [[Federación Agraria Argentina]] of [[Entre Ríos Province|Entre Ríos]] and of the ecology movement of the [[Asamblea Ciudadana Ambiental de Gualeguaychú]]. He became famous during [[2008 Argentine government conflict with the agricultural sector|Argentina's longest farmer strike]], during which he led one of the hardline groups, blocking the strategic [[Ruta Nacional 14 (Argentina)|Ruta Nacional Nº 14]], also known as the Mercosur Road, in [[Gualeguaychú, Entre Ríos|Gualeguaychú]].
==Biography== ===Childhood and youth=== [[Image:Alfredo De Angelis - ruralista.jpg|thumb|left|Alfredo de Angeli, small farmer and businessman, rural leader, member of the [[Federación Agraria Argentina]] (Argentinian Agricultural Federation) of [[Entre Ríos Province|Entre Ríos]].]] One of nine brothers, he was born and spent his early years in the [[Paraná, Entre Ríos|Paraná]] department. In July 1980, he settled in Gualeguaychú, in a town named [[Arroyo El Sauce]]. He has an identical [[twin]] named Atilio, with whom he is usually confused, and who is also his partner in their business society. His twin is the one who dedicates all his time to the agricultural activity, while Alfredo splits his time between his job and his role as rural leader. Their society rents between 675 and 1,100 hectares (according to different sources) to different owners. <ref>''“I've been a settler with the Yabrán family for 10 years.”, says De Angeli'', [http://www.diarioperfil.com.ar/edimp/0255/articulo.php?art=7054&ed=0255] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080525110113/http://www.diarioperfil.com.ar/edimp/0255/articulo.php?art=7054&ed=0255 |date=2008-05-25 }}</ref> They cultivate [[soybean]], [[maize|corn]], [[sunflower]] and [[crop]]. Nowadays he lives in a house near the beach of [[El Ñandubaysal]] at Gualeguaychú.
