'''Wilson Lee Flores''' is a multi-awarded [[writer]], college professor, [[real estate entrepreneur]], economics and geopolitics analyst, baker, art collector, poet and public speaker.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://business.inquirer.net/190732/kamuning-bakerys-wilson-lee-flores|title=Kamuning Bakery’s Wilson Lee Flores|last=Lee-Chua|first=Queena N.|access-date=2018-09-02|language=en}}</ref> 

In December 2013, he bought the pioneer, artisanal [[Kamuning Bakery Cafe]] of [[Quezon City]] and revived it starting January 2014.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thelobbyist.biz/profiles/859-8-things-to-know-about-wilson-lee-flores-and-kamuning-bakery-cafe|title=8 Things to know about Wilson Lee Flores and Kamuning Bakery Café|last=TheLOBBYiST|work=THELOBBYIST|access-date=2018-09-02|language=en-gb}}</ref> 

He has won a record 15 [[Catholic Mass Media Awards]] (CMMA) for his [[Philippine Star]] newspaper columns and three [[Don Carlos Palanca Memorial Awards for Literature]]. He has also been honored with a record three CMMA Hall of Fame Awards, including CMMA Hall of Fame Awards for "Best Opinion Column" and "Best Business Column". <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pressreader.com/philippines/business-world/20180628/282583083746829|title=PressReader.com - Connecting People Through News|website=www.pressreader.com|access-date=2018-09-02}}</ref>  He also writes a Tagalog or Filipino-language column "Kuwentong Panadero" for Philippine Star Group's mass-market [[Pilipino Star Ngayon]] tabloid every Friday.

